subSubSection.paragraph:
This species has sometimes been attributed to Howard Weems as he provided a description of it in his PhD thesis (
Weems 1953
). However, as Weems himself did not consider his thesis a publication in the meaning of the Code (
International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature 1999
), the name has remained a nomen nudum. In the files of the Systematic Entomology Laboratory at the Smithsonian, Chris Thompson found a complete manuscript by his predecessor, Charles T. Greene, written long before the Weems' thesis. Despite having not seeing Greene's work, we have honoured his contribution by including him as an author of the species.

A single specimen was sequenced (Table 
2
).
